{"name": "harlequin-wherobots", "metadata": {"name": "harlequin-wherobots", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["harlequin", "wherobots-python-dbapi"], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733156163}, "documentation": ["# Wherobots Adapter for Harlequin\n\nThis repository provides the Harlequin adapter for WherobotsDB, using\nthe Wherobots Spatial SQL API and its\n[wherobots-python-dbapi-driver](https://github.com/wherobots/wherobots-python-dbapi-driver).\n\n## Installation\n\n```\n$ pip install harlequin-wherobots\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nProcure an API key from Wherobots, and start Harlequin with the\nrequired parameters:\n\n```\n$ harlequin -a wherobots --api-key <key>\n```\n\nAlternatively, you can use your session token:\n\n```\n$ harlequin -a wherobots --token <token>\n```\n\nThe Harlequin adapter for Wherobots will automatically start a Wherobots\nSQL session with the default runtime (Tiny, 4 executors) in the\ndefault Wherobots public compute region (AWS `us-west-2`). You can\noverride those defaults with the `--runtime` and `--region` options,\nrespectively:\n\n```\n$ harlequin -a wherobots --api-key <key> --runtime MEDIUM --region AWS_US_WEST_2\n```\n\n> [!NOTE]\n> Community Edition users of Wherobots Cloud are restricted to the\n> \"Tiny\" runtime size. See our [Pricing](https://www.wherobots.com/pricing)\n> for more information.\n\n## Advanced options\n\nIf your SQL session is already provisioned and running, you can force\nthe driver to directly connect to it via its WebSocket URL (without\nprotocol version):\n\n```\n$ harlequin -a wherobots --api-key <key> --ws-url <session-url>\n```\n\nYou can also specify the base hostname of the Wherobots stack to\ninteract with as the first positional parameter. By default, the driver\nconnects to `cloud.wherobots.com`, the official public Wherobots\nservice.\n\n```\n$ harlequin -a wherobots --api-key <key> [host]\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.token", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.api_key", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.runtime", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.region", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.ws_url", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.cli_options.WHEROBOTS_ADAPTER_OPTIONS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.HarlequinWherobotsAdapter", "xref": {"fqname": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter.HarlequinWherobotsAdapter", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter._log_file", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter._log_debug", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter.HarlequinWherobotsCursor", "bases": ["HarlequinCursor"], "methods": [{"name": "harlequin_wherobots.adapter.HarlequinWherobotsCursor.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cursor", "type": {"name": "Cursor", "xref": {"fqname": "wherobots.db.Cursor", "project": "wherobots-python-dbapi"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documenta